## Remediation

### Fix 1 — Sanitize LLM Output
```
→ Always HTML-encode LLM responses before rendering
→ Implement Content Security Policy (CSP)
→ Never inject raw LLM output directly into the DOM
```

### Fix 2 — Separate Data from Instructions
```
→ Tag external content (reviews) clearly
→ LLM must treat reviews as plain text only
→ Never as executable HTML
```

### Fix 3 — Protect Sensitive Actions
```
→ Account deletion → mandatory confirmation step
→ Irreversible actions → require re-authentication
→ Add CSRF tokens to all sensitive forms
```

### Fix 4 — Output Filtering
```
→ Scan LLM responses before display
→ Detect and neutralize HTML/JS tags
→ Allowlist permitted output formats
```

